Φ(Descriptive_Analytics) = μ(historical_data) → form ⊕ pattern_inventory

Where:
  μ :: event_stream → structured_summary    ("what happened?")
  →  :: form crystallization (retrospective, closed)
  ⊕ :: superposition of metrics, dashboards, mined patterns

Composition:
  descriptive  = μ alone, applied to historical event-stream
  → distinguished from predictive (σ — projection of likely unknowns)
  → distinguished from prescriptive (Ω∘λ — projection ∘ commitment ∘ closure)

Position in the triad:
  μ → σ → (Ω∘λ)
  descriptive → predictive → prescriptive
  form → projection → closure
  what was → what will → what should

Signature:
  μ alone — the analytics frame's first move. The past is given; descriptive
  analytics renders it legible without altering it. The closure here is
  temporal-historical (the past has already closed) rather than participatory
  (action closing the future loop).

  descriptive(data) → form(data)               where form = aggregations, metrics, patterns
  predictive(form, vars) → P(unknown | form)   where prediction depends on descriptive's form
  prescriptive(form, prediction) → action(field)  where action commits and modifies the field

Invariant:
  The descriptive move is fully retrospective and reversible-by-recomputation.
  Different selection choices produce different descriptions of the same data,
  but no descriptive operation alters the underlying historical record.
  The data is closed; the description is editorial.

Consequence:
  Selection is constitutive. Which metrics, which dimensions, which aggregations,
  which time windows — each choice imposes a structure on what would otherwise
  be undifferentiated event-stream. The "what happened" answer is always
  "what was selected to be summarized." This selection is invisible in the
  consumed output (the dashboard) but load-bearing for everything that
  builds on top.

Foundation property:
  All downstream analytics depend on descriptive output. Gaps here propagate
  upward as gaps in predictive substrate and prescriptive recommendation.
  Descriptive is the layer the analytics frame must get right before any
  meaningful projection or closure becomes possible.

| :closed-historical
